## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q1 — Ingest multipart vs JSON**: `POST /api/sources/ingest` currently accepts a JSON body with `fileName`/`mimeType`. Does it accept binary file content via `multipart/form-data`, or does the frontend need to convert to base64? Answer determines `sourcesApi.ts` fetch body construction.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q2 — `WorkflowEditorScreen` router or prop?**: Currently receives `workflows`, `workflowId`, `onSaveWorkflow`, `onCustomize`, `onNavigate` as props passed from the parent route. After Phase 11 removes store-level workflows, should this component use `useQuery` internally (preferred) or continue receiving workflows as props (backward compat)? Recommended: use `useQuery` internally and drop the props — 1 less prop-drilling chain.

> [!NOTE]
> **`LeftNav.tsx` `toStr as any`**: The cast exists because `toStr` is a string assembled at runtime from a union of route paths. The fix is to use `@tanstack/react-router`'s `LinkComponent` with a `to` prop typed as `RegisteredRouter['routePaths']`. This may require the `@tanstack/react-router` path generation to be up-to-date. If `routeTree.gen.ts` is stale, regenerate with `pnpm vite` first.
